I"á<p>The intention of this excersise is to program a basic behaviour of bump-spin using a finite state machine. For that, we will use JdeRobot visualStates tool, that allows you to create your own states machine in an intuitive way.</p>

<p>There is a Kobuki robot inside a labyrinth or scenario. The robot will go front until it gets close to an obstacle. The it will go back, turn a random angle and go front again repeating the process. This exercise aims to show the power of automata when building robot behavior.</p>

